RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE LILIANA broke alertly and disputed the early pace, pressed the fast pace into the turn while outside of DAWN AT LAST, kept pressure on the quick pace along the turn, drew to even terms with DAWN AT LAST into upper stretch and battled with that rival to the furlong marker, took command inside of the furlong pole and drew to a clear lead heading to the sixteenth-marker, came under late pressure from the runner-up and held in a drive at the finish. RAUCOUS TIZZY settled off of the fast early pace while saving ground, improved position while on the rail heading to the quarter marker, tipped two wide for the stretch drive and continued that gain to the furlong pole, rallied in the final sixteenth, pressured the winner in deep stretch but could not get by in the final strides and held safely for second. CRY ME A RUNNER was forwardly placed in the early running and stalked the fast pace into the turn, was steered outside of rivals entering the bend and raced four wide to the quarter marker, came five wide into the stretch and lost ground at the furlong pole, re-rallied while widest in the final sixteenth and won the nod for third on the wire. SMOOVE AS SILK lost her path at the break and was off slowly, was unhurried in the early running and saved ground into the turn, angled three then four wide into the stretch, mounted a late bid in the final sixteenth, raced in traffic in deep stretch and just missed for third. MORO FIRST CLASS raced close to the fast early pace while saving ground, was steered to the three path nearing the top of the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker and was outkicked in the final sixteenth. DAWN AT LAST broke alertly and showed good early speed, set pressed fractions from the inside through the turn, battled with LITTLE LILIANA into the stretch, could not keep pace into the final stages and gave way. CAROLINE MARGARET chased the fast pace from the second flight, came three wide to the quarter marker, was coaxed along five wide into the stretch and did not threaten. NOT NOW I'M BIZZIE lacked early speed, raced five wide into the stretch and did not factor.

HOT RAGEOUS chased the fast early pace from a two wide path, lost ground along the turn, slipped to the inside in upper stretch and re-rallied at the furlong grounds, was gaining in the final stages but was unable to reel in the top three. AMAZEN GRAZEN broke out at the start, made contact with PRIMROSE RIDGE and was off slowly, chased the fast early pace from the back, was steered three wide into the turn and chased to the quarter marker, maintained that three wide position into the stretch, gained ground at the furlong pole and showed good late interest in deep stretch, while unable to threaten the leaders. EM N HOLL'S FIESTA chased the fast early pace from the inside, lost ground on the turn, tipped two wide into upper stretch, was able to mildly re-rally in the final furlong but needed more in the end. BESTRELLA (IRE) chased the fast early pace from the rear, was coaxed four wide along the turn, could not keep pace into the stretch and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1M All Weather Track CR: 81. Claiming Purse 13400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUPLICATION broke a little awkwardly, ducked in and bumped COACH OTT after the start, then was pushed to get good position going into the first turn, was content to stalk the pace from mid-pack down the backstretch, started a rally from the three-furlong pole, came into the stretch three wide and finished well under strong handling to win clear. COOPERKLIMT was aggressively sent for the lead, jumped a shadow just before the six furlong pole, held the lead in hand down the backstretch, repelled a bid by ALGERIA (IRE) on the turn opened up a clear lead in the stretch and outfinished all but the winner. DANCE COMPANY ducked in sharply at the break, causing a chain reaction by impeding DADDY'SDARLINGBOY then bumping TAKE THE TWO TEN forcing that one into ALGERIA (IRE), raced three wide through the first half mile, launched a bid from the seven-sixteenths pole, came under a hard ride near the quarter pole, was kept to task down the lane and outfinished the rest for third. ALGERIA (IRE) stumbled badly at the break then once righted was slammed into by TAKE THE TWO TEN a few strides out, recovered again then stalked COOPERKLIMT to the outside in the early stages, went to press the issue from the half mile pole, got with a neck of that rival passing the quarter pole then drifted wide turning for home, lost momentum and finished evenly. TAKE THE TWO TEN ducked out at the start, made contact with DADDY'SDARLINGBOY then rebounded into the rear of ALGERIA (IRE), allowed to settle then angled in to save ground, raced between horses at the back of the pack through the first turn, then began to make a little forward progress from the nine-sixteenths pole, started a mild rally with three furlongs to run, raced on the wrong lead for most of the stretch run and could find another gear when needed. DADDY'SDARLINGBOY was outrun from the break, took a three wide path through the clubhouse turn, raced outside of a trio of at the rear of the field, struggled to keep up passing the three furlong pole and had nothing to offer in the stretch. COACH OTT broke well but was bumped by DUPLICATION just after the break, then was encouraged to show some speed but was outrun to the first turn, raced near the rear of the field to the half-mile marker, began to lose contact with the field and was not persevered with once hopelessly beaten.
